# Role: seo-optimizer

> **Owns:** Nothing exclusively — this is a cross-cutting lens applied to the public-facing surfaces of 1BT WIKI (homepage feed, article listing/detail, tech-talk listing/detail), which are owned by `analytics-dashboard-engineer`, `content-authoring-engineer`, and `content-publishing-engineer` respectively.
> This file supplements those roles' rules — it doesn't replace their ownership of the underlying pages.

## Role Charter
1BT WIKI's articles and tech talks are internal knowledge content, but discoverability still matters for internal search and any future public exposure. Whoever is touching a public-facing page listed in the globs above should apply these conventions; this is not a standalone owned feature.

## Conventions

### Metadata (Next.js App Router)
- Every page under the globs above must export a `generateMetadata` (dynamic) or `metadata` (static) object — never leave Next.js defaults on a content page.
- Title format: `"{Page Title} · 1BT WIKI"`, kept under ~60 characters.
- Description: derived from the article/tech-talk's own description or the first ~155 characters of plain-text body (use `content-authoring-engineer`'s `extractTextFromTipTap()` utility — don't re-implement text extraction).

```typescript
// src/app/(dashboard)/articles/[id]/page.tsx
export async function generateMetadata({ params }: { params: { id: string } }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const article = await articleApi.getById(params.id);
  return {
    title: `${article.title} · 1BT WIKI`,
    description: extractTextFromTipTap(article.body).slice(0, 155),
  };
}
```

### Structured Data
- Article detail pages should emit `Article` JSON-LD (headline, author, datePublished, dateModified).
- Tech Talk detail pages should emit `Event` JSON-LD (name, startDate, description) when `event_date` is set.
- Only emit structured data for **Published** content — never for Draft/Pending/Rejected.

### Semantic HTML & Accessibility (SEO-adjacent)
- One `<h1>` per page, matching the article/tech-talk title.
- Images (including TipTap-embedded images) must have meaningful `alt` text — never leave `alt=""` on content images.
- Internal links between related articles/techTalks use `<Link>` (Next.js), not full-page `<a>` reloads.

### URLs
- Article and tech talk URLs stay stable once published (`/articles/[id]`, `/techTalks/[id]`) — do not introduce slug changes on edit, since that breaks existing links/bookmarks.

### Sitemap
- `analytics-dashboard-engineer` should ensure published articles and tech talks are included in a generated `sitemap.xml` (Next.js `app/sitemap.ts`), excluding Draft/Pending/Rejected/soft-deleted content.

## Non-Goals
- No SEO changes to authenticated-only surfaces (admin dashboard, reviewer approvals, profile, notifications) — these are never indexed and don't need metadata beyond the app default.

## How to use this file
If your PR touches a file matched by the globs above, apply these conventions in addition to whichever feature role's rules already govern that file (`content-authoring-engineer`, `content-publishing-engineer`, or `analytics-dashboard-engineer`).
